:"circa 1240–Overleden","1240–Male":"1240–Overleden","1244–Female":"1244–Overleden","1280–Male":"1280–Overleden","1200–Male":"1200–Overleden","1204–Female":"1204–Overleden","1204":"1204","1200":"1200","1244":"1244","ABT    1240":"circa 1240","1240":"1240","Abt 1280":"circa 1280","1280":"1280","of,Morgannwg gwlad,Glamorganshire,Wales":"Glamorgan, Wales, Verenigd Koninkrijk","Morgannwg gwlad, Glamorganshire, Wales, United Kingdom":"Glamorgan, Wales, Verenigd Koninkrijk"},"en":{"ABT    1240–":"about 1240–Deceased","1240–Male":"1240–Deceased","1244–Female":"1244–Deceased","1280–Male":"1280–Deceased","1200–Male":"1200–Deceased","1204–Female":"1204–Deceased","1204":"1204","1200":"1200","1244":"1244","ABT    1240":"about 1240","1240":"1240","Abt 1280":"about 1280","1280":"1280","of,Morgannwg gwlad,Glamorganshire,Wales":"Glamorgan, Wales, United Kingdom","Morgannwg gwlad, Glamorganshire, Wales, United Kingdom":"Glamorgan, Wales, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Nicolas","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Spanish Alberto, Angelito, Emilio, Fernando, Francisco, Manuel, Mario, Ricardo, Rodolfo, Ruben, Alfredo, Angel.  French Luc, Pierre, Andre, Georges, Jacques, Marcellin, Yves, Adrien, Alain, Camille, Celina, Dominique.","Spanish (<b>Nicolás</b>), French, Walloon, Breton, and West Indian (mainly Haiti): from the personal name <i>Nicolás</i> (Spanish), <i>Nicolas</i> (French, Breton), from Greek <i>Nikolaos</i> (see   Nicholas  ). In France, this surname is most common in Brittany.","English (southern England and Glamorgan): variant of   Nicholas  ."],"variants":[{"name":"Nicole","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  French Andre, Elzear.","French: from the personal name <i>Nicole</i>, feminine form of   Nicolas  .","English (Middlesex): variant of   Nichol  ."]},{"name":"Loesel","meanings":["German (<b>Lösel</b>): from a pet form of the personal name <i>Nikolaus</i>, German form of   Nicolas  ."]},{"name":"Nykiel","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  Polish Zbigniew, Stanislaw.","Polish: from the personal name <i>Nicolaus</i>, the Latin form of   Nicolas   (Polish <i>Mikołaj</i>), or a Polonized form of German   Nickel  ."]},{"name":"Nicholas","meanings":["English (southwestern England and south Wales) and Dutch: from the personal name <i>Nicholas</i> (from Latin <i>Nicolaus</i>, from Greek <i>Nikolaos</i>, from <i>nikān</i> ‘to conquer’ + <i>laos</i> ‘people’). Forms with <i>-ch-</i> are due to hypercorrection (compare   Anthony  ). The name in various vernacular forms was popular among Christians throughout Europe in the Middle Ages, largely as a result of the fame of a 4th-century Lycian bishop, about whom a large number of legends grew up, and who was venerated in the Orthodox Church as well as the Catholic. In North America, the English form of the surname has absorbed cognates from other languages and also their patronymics and other derivatives, e.g. Croatian and Serbian <b>Nikolić</b> (see   Nikolic  ), Greek <b>Papanikolaou</b> ‘(son of) Nicholas the priest’ and   Nikolopoulos  . Compare   Nickolas  .","History: The colonial official and revolutionary patriot Robert Carter Nicholas was from a prominent VA family on both sides. His father was a British navy surgeon who emigrated <i>c.</i> 1700 from Lancashire, England, to Williamsburg, VA."]}]},{"name":"Iorwerth","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Traditional: from <i>iōr</i>‘ ‘lord’ + a mutated form of <i>berth</i> ‘handsome’; borne in the <i>Mabinogi</i> by the jealous brother of  Madawg , son of  Maredudd . <i>Iorwerth</i> came to be regarded as a Welsh equivalent of  Edward , but it has no actual connection with that name."],"variants":[{"name":"Yorath","meanings":["Anglicized form of   Iorwerth   or, in some cases, a transferred use of the surname derived from it."]}]},{"name":"ap","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["‘Loving’."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Iorwerth ap Nicolas was born about 1240, in Glamorgan, Wales, United Kingdom, his father, Nicolas \" Dean\" ap, was 42 and his mother, Mrs. Nicolas Dean ap, was 38. He had at least 1 son with Mrs. Iorwerth ap Nicolas."},"et":{"ABT    1240–":"umbes 1240–Surnud","1240–Male":"1240–Surnud","1244–Female":"1244–Surnud","1280–Male":"1280–Surnud","1200–Male":"1200–Surnud","1204–Female":"1204–Surnud","1204":"1204","1200":"1200","1244":"1244","ABT    1240":"umbes 1240","1240":"1240","Abt 1280":"umbes 1280","1280":"1280","of,Morgannwg gwlad,Glamorganshire,Wales":"Glamorgan, Wales, United Kingdom","Morgannwg gwlad, Glamorganshire, Wales, United Kingdom":"Glamorgan, Wales, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"ABT    1240–":"noin 1240–Kuollut","1240–Male":"1240–Kuollut","1244–Female":"1244–Kuollut","1280–Male":"1280–Kuollut","1200–Male":"1200–Kuollut","1204–Female":"1204–Kuollut","1204":"1204","1200":"1200","1244":"1244","ABT    1240":"noin 1240","1240":"1240","Abt 1280":"noin 1280","1280":"1280","of,Morgannwg gwlad,Glamorganshire,Wales":"Glamorgan, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Morgannwg gwlad, Glamorganshire, Wales, United Kingdom":"Glamorgan, Wales, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"ABT    1240–":"environ 1240–Décédé","1240–Male":"1240–Décédé","1244–Female":"1244–Décédée","1280–Male":"1280–Décédé","1200–Male":"1200–Décédé","1204–Female":"1204–Décédée","1204":"1204","1200":"1200","1244":"1244","ABT    1240":"environ 1240","1240":"1240","Abt 1280":"environ 1280","1280":"1280","of,Morgannwg gwlad,Glamorganshire,Wales":"Glamorgan, Pays de Galles, Royaume-Uni","Morgannwg gwlad, Glamorganshire, Wales, United Kingdom":"Glamorgan, Pays de Galles, Royaume-Uni","lifeSummary":"Lorsque Iorwerth ap Nicolas est né environ 1240, à Glamorgan, Pays de Galles, Royaume-Uni, son père, Nicolas \" Dean\" ap, avait 42 ans 